      "content": "but isn't there a difference between a \"debate\" and something that's just a matter of fact? like, if we look at how most developed, high-income countries actually function, they've already leaned into the idea that healthcare is a public service. doesn't that move the conversation past \"which values do we prioritize\" and actually make the \"inefficient takeover\" argument look more like an outdated talking point rather than a valid economic theory? like, isn't the trend clearly pointing towards healthcare being a right?",
